100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 11, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, addressing ongoing tensions in Europe and efforts to promote disarmament. In the United States, the trial of the "Scopes Monkey Trial" continued in Dayton, Tennessee, drawing national attention to the debate over evolution in schools. Meanwhile, in Egypt, unrest persisted as nationalists demanded independence from British rule, reflecting growing anti-colonial sentiments across the globe.
